'''Michael Ngaleku Shirima''' (born 1943) is a [[Tanzania]]n [[businessman]], [[entrepreneur]], and [[philanthropist]]. He is the founder and current [[chairman]] of [[Precision Air]], Tanzania's largest privately owned airline.<ref>[http://www.lusakatimes.com/2010/07/15/tanzanian-airline-eyes-zambia/ Michael Shirima Is Chairman of Precision Air]</ref>
==Background== He was born in Usseri Rombo District, [[Kilimanjaroo Region]], Tanzania.<ref>[http://www.100people.org/schools_page.php?row=15&viewschool=337 Interview at 100 People.com]</ref> He is of [[Chaga people|Chaga]] ethnicity.{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}
==Education== The details of his education are not publicly available.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}
==Career== Shirima started [[Precision Air]] in 1993, with a twin-engine five-seater airplane, a [[Piper PA-23|Piper Aztec]]. Using [[Arusha]] as its base, the airline began by providing [[charter flight]]s to tourists visiting [[Serengeti National Park]], [[Ngorongoro Crater]], the island of [[Unguja]], and other tourist attractions in Tanzania. As customer numbers grew, the airline acquired more equipment and began scheduled flights maintaining Arusha as its base.<ref>[http://www.precisionairtz.com/index.php?page=company-profile Shirima Founded Precision Air In 1993]</ref> In 2003, Kenya Airways, the largest airline in [[East Africa]], acquired 49% shareholding in Precision Air for a cash sum of US$2 million.<ref>[http://www.emeraldinsight.com/case_studies.htm?articleid=1917143&show=html Kenya Airlines Paid US$2 million for 49% Shareholding In Precision Air]</ref>
Precision Air is headquartered in [[Dar es Salaam]], the largest city in Tanzania. In October 2011, Precision Air floated 30.35 percent shareholding in the airline stock, in an [[Initial Public Offering]] on the [[Dar es Salaam Stock Exchange]].<ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/201110180022.html Precision Air Becomes A Publicly Traded Company]</ref> {{asof|June 2012}}, Kenyan press reports indicated that Michael Shirima is the largest shareholder in the [[stock]] of the airline with 42.91 percent shareholding.<ref>[http://www.businessdailyafrica.com/Precision+Air+gets+Sh510+million+IFC+boost+/-/539552/1427660/-/item/0/-/144vf5sz/-/index.html Shareholding In Precision Air In June 2012]</ref>
==Other responsibilities== In addition to his aviation interests, Shirima owns five percent of the stock of [[I&M Bank (Tanzania)]], a medium-sized commercial bank. As of December 2011, the bank's total assets were valued at about US$130 million (TZS:200 billion) and the bank's shareholders' equity had approximately US$15 million (TZS:23 billion).<ref>[http://www.imbank.com/TZ/?od=report December 2011 Financial Report] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130126020326/http://www.imbank.com/TZ/?od=report |date=2013-01-26 }}</ref> He also sits on the [[Board of Directors]] of the same bank.<ref>[http://www.imbank.com/TZ/?od=director Michael Shirima Is Board Member of I&M Bank Tanzania] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130126072629/http://www.imbank.com/TZ/?od=director |date=2013-01-26 }}</ref>
He is the founder and [[proprietor]] of Cornelius Ngaleku Orphanage, located in Useri Division, [[Rombo|Rombo District]], [[Kilimanjaro Region]], in northern Tanzania. The [[orphanage]] looks after homeless children picked up on the streets of Tanzanian cities.<ref>[http://in2%20eastafrica.net/call-for-voluntary-care-of-street-orphaned-children/ Shirima Is Founder of Cornelius Ngaleku Orphanage]</ref> Shirima also serves as the Chairman of Tanzania Golf Union (TGU).<ref>[http://www.arushatimes.co.tz/2006/28/sports_1.htm Shirima Was Chairman of TGU In 2006]</ref>
